    <note>Zhao(1) Zonghui(2) [19411] I am identifying him as the founder of a separate lineage since this is the only way to link his 5th generation descendant, Shansheng [19427] (great grandson of Zhongyuan [19415], who was Zonghui(2)'s #2 son), and Shansheng's adopted heir, Rugu [19434], who was Zonghui(2)'s 6th generation descendant and the 5th generation descendant of Zonghui(2)'s #1 son, Zhongsun [19412]. This will be jia 'a' of lineage #1234. The imperial genealogy mingzi of his #3 son, Zhongshen [20442], as well as himself, who were respectively grandfather and great grandfather of Shifen [20443], whose title correctly identifies him as the father-in-law of Liu(2) Bangguang [20447] (q.v.) differs from the mingzi in Lu(9) Zuqian's [7055] funerary inscription for Bangguang (Zonghui(2) is identfied as Zongxuan, and the second character in Zhongshen's mingzi uses radical 149 instead of 85). SS(PRC), 230.7264. CBD, 4, 3504-5.</note>
